Pattern 1: Frequency Based (Counting)
You need to know exactly how many times an element appears. This is the most common use case for a HashMap.

The Concept: Iterate through the array/string. Store the element as the key, and increment its count as the value.

Java Blueprint:

Java

Map<Integer, Integer> freqMap = new HashMap<>();
for (int num : nums) {
    // getOrDefault prevents NullPointerExceptions if the key doesn't exist yet
    freqMap.put(num, freqMap.getOrDefault(num, 0) + 1);
}
Essential Interview Questions:

Easy: Valid Anagram (LeetCode 242) - Count frequencies of String A, subtract frequencies using String B. If all values are 0, it's an anagram.

Medium: Top K Frequent Elements (LeetCode 347) - Build the frequency map, then pass the map's keys into a PriorityQueue (Min-Heap) to find the top K.

Medium: Sort Characters By Frequency (LeetCode 451)
